### NetSuite SOD RESTlet - Test Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar HTTP client

### Variables (update these with your values)
@account = 1234567
@script = 123
@deploy = 1
@baseUrl = https://{{account}}.restlets.api.netsuite.com/app/site/hosting/restlet.nl

### =============================================================================
### GET Requests
### =============================================================================

### 1. Basic GET - Fetch all active users (default settings)
GET {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth realm="{{account}}",oauth_consumer_key="YOUR_CONSUMER_KEY",oauth_token="YOUR_TOKEN_ID",oauth_signature_method="HMAC-SHA256",oauth_timestamp="1234567890",oauth_nonce="random_nonce",oauth_version="1.0",oauth_signature="YOUR_SIGNATURE"

### 2. GET with Query Parameters - Fetch with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}&status=ACTIVE&limit=50&offset=0
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

### 3. GET Inactive Users
GET {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}&status=INACTIVE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

### =============================================================================
### POST Requests (Recommended - More Control)
### =============================================================================

### 1. Basic POST - Fetch first 10 users with permissions
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "limit": 10,
  "offset": 0,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 2. POST with Subsidiary Filter
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "subsidiary": "United States",
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 0,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 3. POST with Department Filter
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "department": "Finance",
  "limit": 50,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 4. POST with Multiple Filters
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "subsidiary": "United States",
  "department": "Finance",
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 0,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 5. POST WITHOUT Permissions (Faster Query)
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "limit": 500,
  "includePermissions": false
}

### 6. POST with Pagination - Page 1
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 0,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 7. POST with Pagination - Page 2
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "limit": 100,
  "offset": 100,
  "includePermissions": true
}

### 8. POST Including Inactive Users
POST {{baseUrl}}?script={{script}}&deploy={{deploy}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: OAuth ...

{
  "includeInactive": true,
  "limit": 200,
  "includePermissions": false
}

